Some residents of Ekiti State, including a lawyer, who were kidnapped a few days ago at Ijesa Isu, in Ikole Local Government Area have been released by their abductors. The four victims were abducted on their way to Ado Ekiti from Omuo Oke. The Public Relations Officer of the Ekiti State Police Command, ASP Sunday Abutu confirmed to DAILY POST that the victims were released through a combined effort of the police, the family and other security agents. He said “They have all been released today at about 18:00hrs through the combined efforts of the police, the military, Amotekun, local hunters, as well as the family members. “Effort is still ongoing for the possible arrest of the culprits.”